well I would say 99% of people don't pluck the lead from walls, hills or the ground. I don't know if anyone melts the brass, but if it starts to crack you can't really reuse it so it normally get's thrown out. Public shooting ranges have a plague known as either "brass hawks" or "brass jews" who go to the range just to steal brass off the ground, they are really annoying. Also a lot of ranges take spent brass left behind, make their own (normally shitty) ammo, and sell it.
